A simple Minecraft plugin for Paper 1.21 that launches players when they step on Gold Pressure Plates.

## Features

- Players are launched 2 blocks high and 5 blocks forward when stepping on Gold Pressure Plates
- Plays "Firework Blast" sound effect when launched
- Spawns "Cloud" particles at player's feet during launch
- Prevents fall damage for 5 seconds after being launched
- Uses modern Paper API 1.21 and Java 21
- **NEW COMMANDS**: `/launch` command with toggle, height, distance, and status options
- Cooldown system to prevent spam launching
- Individual player settings for launch height and distance
- Permission-based command access

## Installation

1. Download the latest JAR file from the [Releases](https://github.com/yourusername/SimpleLaunch/releases) page
2. Place the JAR file in your server's `plugins` folder
3. Restart your Paper server
4. The plugin will automatically enable

## Usage

### Basic Usage
Simply place Gold Pressure Plates on your server. When players step on them, they will be launched according to the configured parameters.

### Commands

**/launch** - Control your SimpleLaunch settings
- `/launch toggle` - Enable/disable launch for yourself
- `/launch height <value>` - Set launch height (1-10, default: 2)
- `/launch distance <value>` - Set launch distance (1-20, default: 5)
- `/launch status` - Show your current settings

**/launchreload** - Reload the plugin (requires `simplelaunch.reload` permission)

### Permissions

- `simplelaunch.reload` - Allows reloading the plugin (default: op)
- `simplelaunch.bypass` - Bypass all restrictions (default: false)

## Configuration

This plugin doesn't require any configuration files. All settings are stored per-player and can be modified using the `/launch` command.

## Building from Source

1. Install Java 21 JDK
2. Install Maven
3. Clone this repository
4. Run `mvn clean package`
5. The JAR file will be created in the `target` directory

